# Subsets Problem - Backtracking Solution

## ğŸ“‹ Problem Description
Given an integer array `nums` of unique elements, return all possible subsets (the power set).

## ğŸ§  Solution Approach
**Backtracking** with include/exclude pattern for each element.

## â±ï¸ Complexity Analysis
- **Time Complexity:** O(2â¿ Ã— n) where n = array length
- **Space Complexity:** O(n) for recursion stack

## ğŸ“Š Example
**Input:** `[1, 2, 3]`
**Output:** `[[], [1], [2], [1,2], [3], [1,3], [2,3], [1,2,3]]`


## ğŸ’¡ Key Points
- Uses backtracking to explore all possibilities
- Creates deep copies to avoid modification issues
- Clear include/exclude pattern for each element

## ğŸ·ï¸ Tags
`#backtracking` `#recursion` `#leetcode` `#subsets` `#java`

## ğŸ“ Java Implementation

```java
import java.util.*;

class Solution {
    /**
     * Main method to generate all subsets
     * @param nums Input array of unique integers
     * @return List of all subsets
     */
    public List<List<Integer>> subsets(int[] nums) {
        List<List<Integer>> result = new ArrayList<>();
        ArrayList<Integer> currentSubset = new ArrayList<>();
        generateSubsets(nums, currentSubset, 0, result);
        return result;
    }
    
    /**
     * Backtracking helper function
     * @param nums Original array
     * @param current Current subset being built
     * @param index Current position in array
     * @param result List to store all subsets
     */
    private void generateSubsets(int[] nums, ArrayList<Integer> current, 
                                int index, List<List<Integer>> result) {
        // Base case: processed all elements
        if (index == nums.length) {
            // IMPORTANT: Create a new copy to avoid modification
            result.add(new ArrayList<>(current));
            return;
        }
        
        // CHOICE 1: Include current element
        current.add(nums[index]);
        generateSubsets(nums, current, index + 1, result);
        
        // Backtrack: remove last element
        current.remove(current.size() - 1);
        
        // CHOICE 2: Exclude current element
        generateSubsets(nums, current, index + 1, result);
    }
}
